	   <tr><td colspan=2>The named Cents are a long wait.&nbsp;&nbsp;perhaps on the order of once per every other day, unless you are clearing the whole zone so as to force a quillimane spawn.  Best chance, simply bind yourself nearby and every time you die, just run across the bridge into South Karana and sweep the zone while tracking for them .. until your group's cleric rezzes you and you go back to your group.  Same method as Stormfeather in IC.<br><br>If you are soloing it, I have found the named cents in the southern half of the zone 4 out of 6 times, although they do move arounds a lot (too many days spent helping mage friends with Quillimane ...)<br><br>Bows dropped 100% of the time<br><br>Happy hunting dear<br>-------------------------<br><br>P.S -- these chaps hit rather hard and are underconned for their level.  You will require help until you are about level 53ish.  After that it is a safe solo<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Feb 24 02:09:11 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Huntress Samanthie Snowheart<br>Half-elf Karana Warder of Surefall Glade<br>65 seasons and more -- sniffing the trails of Norrath<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=369799" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=369799</a></td></tr>
